{{Dialogue a-b|Jon Snow|My father was [[Eddard Stark|Ned Stark]]. I have the blood of the First Men. My ancestors lived here, same as yours!|Ygritte|So why're you fightin' us?|[[Jon Snow]], a [[Northmen|Northman]], and [[Ygritte]], of the [[Free Folk]].|A Man Without Honor}}

The '''First Men''' are the original human inhabitants of [[Westeros]]. They ruled the continent for millennia before the [[Andals]] invaded from the eastern continent of [[Essos]]. The Andals overran most of southern Westeros, but failed to take [[the North]]. While the blood of the First Men and the Andals has intermingled over thousands of years of dynastic [[Marriage|marriages]], the [[Northmen|inhabitants]] of the North have the greatest amount of First Men blood in their veins and keep their traditions.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Complete Guide to Westeros]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref name=&quot;VG Westeros Through The Ages&quot;&gt;[http://viewers-guide.hbo.com/game-of-thrones/season2/#!/guide/appendix/beyond-the-houses/ HBO Viewer's Guide, Season 2 appendices Westeros Through the Ages]&lt;/ref&gt;
